{{Slavic Native Faith}}
'''Ivanovism''' ([[Russian language|Russian]]: Ивановизм), also known by the name of the followers, the '''Ivanovites''' (Ивановцы), is a [[religion|religious]] movement in [[Russia]] based on the teachings of the [[mysticism|mystic]] [[Porfiry Ivanov]] and his "natural healing system".<ref>БалагушкинРНСР, 2002, с. 108</ref> The movement is classified as [[syncretism|syncretic]].<ref>Верейкина, 2004, с. 37</ref> Central to the movement is the ''Detka'' (Детка) healing system<ref>Балагушкин, 2008, с. 475</ref> and a "Hymn to Life" (Гимн жизни) focused on religious ideas.<ref>Балагушкин, 2008, с. 475</ref>

The Ivanovite movement is categorised among Russian [[new religious movements]]<ref>Балагушкин, 1999</ref><ref>КантеровНРД, 2001, с. 61—72</ref><ref>Кантеров, 2006, с. 707</ref><ref>Балагушкин, 2008, с. 476</ref> as [[Neopaganism|Neopagan]]<ref>КантеровНРД, 2001, с. 61 — 72</ref><ref>Мильков, 2002, с. 295</ref><ref>Shnirelman, 2005, с. 1188</ref> with neo-[[Christianity|Christian]] elements.<ref>Балагушкин, 1999</ref>

